The paper focuses on a robot box pushing task, which is a problem in robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning algorithms is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the paper specifically compares different reinforcement learning algorithms. The comparison of algorithms involves analyzing their performance, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The problem is also structured as a multi-agent problem, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the dynamic environment in which the algorithms are tested involves the interaction between agents and objects, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
